# Mail System Automation Analysis

## 1. Catalyst Application Structure

### User Signup Logic

**File: `/home/shanta/PycharmProjects/comserv2/Comserv/lib/Comserv/Controller/HostingSignup.pm`**

This controller handles user registration and domain provisioning:

```perl
# Process the signup form submission
sub process_signup :Path('process') :Args(0) {
    my ($self, $c) = @_;

    # Get form data
    my $params = $c->request->params;

    # Create the user
    my $user_data = {
        username => $params->{username},
        password => $params->{password},
        email => $params->{email},
        first_name => $params->{first_name},
        last_name => $params->{last_name},
        roles => 'normal', # Default role for new users
    };

    my $user = $c->model('User')->create_user($user_data);

    # Create the site
    my $site_data = {
        name => $params->{site_name},
        description => $params->{site_description} || "Created via hosting signup",
        /* ... other site fields ... */
    };

    my $site = $c->model('Site')->add_site($c, $site_data);

    # Add the domain to the site
    if ($site) {
        my $domain_data = {
            site_id => $site->id,
            domain => $params->{domain_name},
        };

        my $domain = $c->model('DBEncy::SiteDomain')->create($domain_data);

        # Mail account creation via Virtualmin API - MISSING INTEGRATION WITH DNS
        try {
            # Create mail account using Virtualmin API
            my $mail_result = $c->model('Mail')->create_mail_account(
                $c, 
                $params->{email}, 
                $params->{password}, 
                $params->{domain_name}
            );

            if ($mail_result) {
                # Send welcome email
                $c->forward('Mail', 'send_welcome_email', [$user]);
            }
        } catch {
            # Log error and continue with signup process
        }
    }
}
```

