### 2. DKIM Key Generation and Management

**Required Components:**
- DKIM model for generating and managing keys:
  ```perl
  package Comserv::Model::DKIM;
  use Moose;
  use namespace::autoclean;
  use Crypt::OpenSSL::RSA;
  use MIME::Base64;
  use Try::Tiny;
  use Comserv::Util::Logging;

  extends 'Catalyst::Model';

  has 'logging' => (
      is => 'ro',
      default => sub { Comserv::Util::Logging->instance }
  );

  # Method to generate DKIM keys
  sub generate_dkim_keys {
      my ($self, $c, $domain, $selector) = @_;

      $selector ||= strftime("%Y%m", localtime);

      try {
          my $rsa = Crypt::OpenSSL::RSA->generate_key(2048);
          my $private_key = $rsa->get_private_key_string();
          my $public_key = $rsa->get_public_key_string();

          # Format public key for DNS
          my $dns_txt = $public_key;
          $dns_txt =~ s/-----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----//;
          $dns_txt =~ s/-----END PUBLIC KEY-----//;
          $dns_txt =~ s/\s+//g;

          return {
              selector => $selector,
              private_key => $private_key,
              public_key => $public_key,
              dns_txt => "v=DKIM1; k=rsa; p=$dns_txt"
          };
      } catch {
          $self->logging->log_with_details($c, 'error', __FILE__, __LINE__, 'generate_dkim_keys', 
              "Failed to generate DKIM keys: $_");
          return;
      };
  }

  __PACKAGE__->meta->make_immutable;
  1;
  ```
- Integration with Virtualmin API to install keys
- Storage of keys in the database

